[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three seriously hurt in two-vehicle crash on A71 in Livingston

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two women and a man have been taken to hospital with serious injuries after a crash on the A71 in Livingston.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The collision, which involved two vehicles, happened at about 13:40 west of the Lizzie Bryce roundabout near Dedridge.
The A71 has been closed eastbound from Newpark roundabout and westbound at the Lizzie Bryce roundabout.
Police said it would remain shut for several hours to allow crash investigations to be carried out.
Officers appealed for witnesses to contact them.
